 @Surfer Rosa  That scene was actually a meme for a long time. Even prior to the internet. It was known as one of the worst fight scenes in film. It was parodied by many cartoons like the Simpsons. It’s funny because it’s such a goofy scene for such a serious film.

I wouldn’t put Godfather in my top ten. I do like the second one better. You should give that one a try. It’s a lot more exciting in the beginning. You get to see Marlon Brando young in the early 1920/30 or whatever. There is some really suspenseful scenes I love. But even then, it wouldn’t be in my top ten.
Definitely in my top 100 somewhere. I can see why you think it’s slow. It’s a valid argument. I LOVE Amadeus! Sooo much. Now that would be up there for me. But I do like long movies like Gone with the Wind and Lawrence of Arabia

