No, I don't think its necessary. I'm not the one who posted a video titled: The 30 greatest films, and left the ability to comment on the video. There are modern masterpieces. Perhaps the word modern might be a bit vague for you but it doesn't mean in the last ten years. My point is just because a movie was made 50, 60, 70 years ago does not mean it is greater than movies that come long after it. Another film that is oddly missing from this list is Stalker. it is a clear masterpiece. Gone with the wind..? Godfather? really? No. This is a definitive title. And a tab bit arrogant one. Maybe it should read "Our list of the 30 greatest films." 


Why is everyone so butt-hurt on youtube. My original comment stands as an observation of this list. And clearly, not one person understood the point.
